               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl744-1">AMS, IV, 507-665 ; BHO, 1121- 26. S. Ashbrook Harvey, dans VC 42 (1988), 376-94. Thad. anglaise des vies grecques et syriaque : R. Doran, The Lives of Simeon Stylites (Kalamazoo, 1992). BS, XI, 1116- 38 (D . Stiernon).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Simeon the Stylite was a shepherd who became a monk.  He lived first in a cistern, but then later built a column on which he lived at Telanesios.  His pillar and extreme asceticism attracted pilgrims and converts.</note>
